<subSubSection id="C3718E97FFDEFFD0C5B06320FC8C999A" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD4DD1CFFDEFFD0C5B06320FC8C999A" blockId="1.[160,1155,1352,1447]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDEFFD0C5B06320FEEE995F" bold="true" box="[160,291,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of this genus is derived from the Salazie Nature Trail, a narrow path through various landscape patches on Praslin, 
<collectingCountry id="F37C9D8CFFDEFFD0C7FF6304FCAB99B8" box="[751,870,1388,1413]" name="Seychelles" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
, where the 
<typeStatus id="54D063BEFFDEFFD0C6FB6304FBD099B8" box="[1003,1053,1388,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDEFFD0C5B063E6FE47999A" box="[160,394,1422,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Salaziella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praslinensis">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDEFFD0C5B063E6FE47999A" box="[160,394,1422,1447]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312">Salaziella praslinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3718E97FFDEFFD3C5B063BEFF299D80" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="1313" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD4DD1CFFDEFFD3C5B063BEFF299D80" blockId="1.[160,1156,1494,1728]" lastBlockId="2.[160,1156,142,445]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="1313" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDEFFD0C5B063BEFED799CD" bold="true" box="[160,282,1494,1520]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new genus could be distinguished other 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDEFFD0C68363BFFC3A99CD" authorityName="Muir" authorityYear="1918" box="[915,1015,1495,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Zoraidini">Zoraidini</taxonomicName>
based on a combination of the following characters: head narrower than pronotum; vertex two times as long as broad, tapering anteriorly, with large V-shaped impression dorsally, anterior margin rounded; frons with gradually widening lateral carinae in the upper part; tegmen with ScP + R three-furcate basally (short ScP + RA1 arising at the middle of the tegmen and elongate RA2 without furcation), media posterior vein with eight branches (MP1 four-furcate, MP2 bifurcate, MP3 and MP4 simple), CuA three-furcate (CuA and MP3 + 4 fused basally). The new genus is habitually similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDDFFD3C68B66E6FF1A9CF7" authority="Van Stalle, 1984" authorityName="Van Stalle" authorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Zorabana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDDFFD3C68B66E6FBC89C9A" box="[923,1029,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313">Zorabana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFAA0EDFFDDFFD3C11E66E6FF1A9CF7" author="Van Stalle J" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" pagination="1 - 61" refId="ref5244" refString="Van Stalle J. 1984. New and interesting African Derbidae (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea). Bull Inst R Sci Nat Belg. 55 (1): 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="1984">Van Stalle, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDDFFD3C40C66D9FE2A9CF7" authority="Stal, 1856" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1856" box="[284,487,177,202]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Helcita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDDFFD3C40C66D9FEAA9CF7" box="[284,359,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313">Helcita</emphasis>
Stal, 1856
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDDFFD3C71B66D9FD2B9CF7" authority="Distant, 1906" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1906" box="[523,742,177,202]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Jada" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDDFFD3C71B66D9FDF29CF7" box="[523,575,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313">Jada</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFAA0EDFFDDFFD3C75C66D9FD2B9CF7" author="Distant WL" box="[588,742,177,202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" pagination="503" refId="ref4366" refString="Distant WL. 1906. Rhynchota. Vol. III (Heteroptera - Homoptera). The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. London (UK): Taylor &amp; Francis; p. 503." type="book chapter" year="1906">Distant, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
] by having a head narrower than pronotum and frons with gradually widening lateral carinae in the upper part. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDDFFD3C5B0669EFEC79D32" authorityName="Van Stalle" authorityYear="1984" box="[160,266,246,271]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Zorabana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDDFFD3C5B0669EFEC79D32" box="[160,266,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313">Zorabana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a simpler venation of tegmen, with media posterior vein having six branches: MP1 bifurcate and other MP branches simple (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFAA0EDFFDDFFD3C60B6771FC079D0F" author="Van Stalle J" box="[795,970,281,306]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" pagination="1 - 61" refId="ref5244" refString="Van Stalle J. 1984. New and interesting African Derbidae (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea). Bull Inst R Sci Nat Belg. 55 (1): 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="1984">Van Stalle 1984</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDDFFD3C6EB6771FBB19D0F" authority=", MP" authorityName="MP" box="[1019,1148,281,306]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Helcita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDDFFD3C6EB6771FB8B9D0F" box="[1019,1094,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313">Helcita</emphasis>
, MP
</taxonomicName>
1 and MP3 bifurcate, other MP branches simple. Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDDFFD3C7F46754FC839D68" authorityName="Van Stalle" authorityYear="1984" box="[740,846,316,341]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Zorabana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDDFFD3C7F46754FC839D68" box="[740,846,316,341]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313">Zorabana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BA69FFFDDFFD3C6966754FC1C9D68" box="[902,977,316,341]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Helcita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91F010EFFDDFFD3C6966754FC1C9D68" box="[902,977,316,341]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313">Helcita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share antennae with first segment short, cylindrical, and second segment round, while the new genus shares first and second segments long, cylindrical (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFAA0EDFFDDFFD3C7CB67E9FCA69DA7" author="Distant WL" box="[731,875,385,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" pagination="503" refId="ref4366" refString="Distant WL. 1906. Rhynchota. Vol. III (Heteroptera - Homoptera). The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. London (UK): Taylor &amp; Francis; p. 503." type="book chapter" year="1906">Distant 1906</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFAA0EDFFDDFFD3C66767E9FBC59DA7" author="Metcalf ZP" box="[887,1032,385,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" pagination="1 - 212" refId="ref5039" refString="Metcalf ZP. 1945. Part 4. Derbidae. In: Metcalf ZP, editor. General Catalogue of the Homoptera. Fascicule IV. Raleigh: North Carolina State College; p. 1 - 212." type="book chapter" year="1945">Metcalf 1945</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFAA0EDFFDDFFD3C10567E9FF1A9D80" author="Van Stalle J" pageId="2" pageNumber="1313" pagination="1 - 61" refId="ref5244" refString="Van Stalle J. 1984. New and interesting African Derbidae (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea). Bull Inst R Sci Nat Belg. 55 (1): 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="1984">Van Stalle 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
